One idea that connects to your earlier discussions is to treat truth as something we converge toward rather than something we possess. Different perspectives can reveal different parts of the same phenomenon. If participants are genuinely trying to update their models instead of simply winning, disagreement becomes a tool for refinement rather than a contest.

That doesn’t guarantee everyone will agree, but it shifts the goal from “defeat the other side” to “reduce error together.”